Some students quietly rehearsed their elevator pitches against the wall while others marked target employers on the event map. Near the stage, the engineering society sponsored a resume review table, fostering networking and professional development. As the lively lunchtime pitch session concluded, students exited the venue carrying tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, stacks of business cards, promotional materials, and resumes inside branded folders, reflecting their engagement and marking the end of a day enriched by diverse offerings.
